trans-unit.source: The <codeInline>ILearner</codeInline> interface provides methods and properties that are used to configure and interact with machine learning models.
trans-unit.target: The <codeInline>ILearner</codeInline> interface provides methods and properties that are used to configure and interact with machine learning models.

trans-unit.source: A learner is defined as a set of instructions that perform standardized machine learning tasks.
trans-unit.target: A learner is defined as a set of instructions that perform standardized machine learning tasks.

trans-unit.source: Learners include classification algorithms, clustering algorithms, and regression algorithms.
trans-unit.target: Learners include classification algorithms, clustering algorithms, and regression algorithms.

trans-unit.source: For a list of learners provided by Azure Machine Learning, see <link xlink:href="0c67013c-bfbc-428b-87f3-f552d8dd41f6" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Initialize</link>.
trans-unit.target: For a list of learners provided by Azure Machine Learning, see <link xlink:href="0c67013c-bfbc-428b-87f3-f552d8dd41f6" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Initialize</link>.

trans-unit.source: This interface encapsulates the following functionality:
trans-unit.target: This interface encapsulates the following functionality:

trans-unit.source: Gets the capabilities of the learner.
trans-unit.target: Gets the capabilities of the learner.

trans-unit.source: These are any general properties of the learner that are not captured by the type signature of the specific learner.
trans-unit.target: These are any general properties of the learner that are not captured by the type signature of the specific learner.

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the settings of the learner.
trans-unit.target: Gets or sets the settings of the learner.

trans-unit.source: The settings are unique to each learner and must be configured once before any query methods can be called on the learner.
trans-unit.target: The settings are unique to each learner and must be configured once before any query methods can be called on the learner.
